==================== Context Pilot — IT delivery sheet ====================

  Unit               : {{ inventory_hostname }}
  Day-0 setup URL    : http://{{ ansible_host | default(inventory_hostname) }}:80

  Vendor (superadmin) account — provider secrets, invisible to the client:
    Email    : {{ cp_seed_superadmin_email }}
    Password : {{ cp_seed_superadmin_password }}

  Client admin account — manages users/agents + IT infra (certs, network):
    Email    : {{ cp_seed_admin_email }}
    Password : {{ cp_seed_admin_password }}

  These passwords are UNIQUE to this unit and are NOT stored anywhere else.
  Keep this sheet physically secure; shred it once setup is complete.

  First-time setup (over the LAN, cleartext http day-0):
    1. Open the day-0 setup URL above (plain http — there is no cert yet).
    2. Sign in with the CLIENT admin email + password above; change the
       password (and set a real admin email) when prompted.
    3. Name the box (DNS name / IP). Saving issues the TLS certificate and
       brings the secure cockpit up on https://<name> (port 443).
    4. Download the CA root and push it to your clients (GPO/MDM), verifying
       the displayed fingerprint. From then on use https://<name>.

